SIMPLE: mawkish
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mawkish
<hw>Mawk"ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Orig., maggoty. See
<er>Mawk</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Apt to cause satiety or loathing;
nauseous; slightly nauseating; disgusting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So sweetly <qex>mawkish'</qex>, and so smoothly dull.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Easily disgusted; squeamish; sentimentally
fastidious.</def> <rj><au>J. H. Newman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Weakly sentimental; maudlin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mawkishly</ent>⟦br⟧
